profile.name: Ouoertheo
profile.blurb: Introspective, meddlesome, music loving, challenge seeking, relaxation aficionado, with an eye towards the sky and a good partner to keep the feet on the ground. Outside the rush, can be found tucked in a corner with an audiobook and a writing utensil, recording riffs and rhythms, or coding for pleasure. In the rush can be found harassing developers, pondering complex systems performance, cooking and baking up a storm in the kitchen, and generally, as an old friend and roommate put it, ‘suckin the day’s...’ actually, i shouldn’t finish that quote.

7269ac33-abfd-4914-892e-a90c1e2c2ac8.text: I also quit and smoked a few cigarettes, but I got lucky, they made me sick and that seemed to cut the loop. Everybody's got their tipping point I guess.

ac6d8a99-b96e-4367-b7d4-856fc91042c6.text: All good :-) this habitica client is a little slow. Glad to hear youre staying on the train for the most part. Never give up! Fun fact: cigarettes have polonium210 in them, it's a radioactive isotope!

d59e2788-5c57-41ca-a717-6f1170a64ff7.text: You ever make it with the not smoking thing?

54dbfe55-37f9-4b23-8027-75d91d6485eb.text: i left that party cuz cyndie's not playing anymore. i can send you a new party invite once you leave the current one.

0692e8ab-2a12-4893-ab9a-43f2c4a2e5ba.text: You gonna accept the new quest?

9de95b3c-4919-4c00-bde0-ef3501bc703d.text: Good on you for that you try to end this horrible bad habit.

3d9cf83a-9ff0-4be3-8813-c42e58864951.text: I smoked about half a pack a day for 14 years. My motivation to stop smoking was my health and how I felt. It caused tense jaw, my insides felt like they were being embalmed, and my sense of smell and taste we're about half what they should be. I also don't appreciate the brainwashing that went into making cigarettes socially acceptable, and now that they aren't really socially acceptable in my city (Austin) it was getting to be an awkward experience in general.

1338eba8-6e6c-4517-ae3d-99c148c57c4e.text: Hi, thanks for the motivation. I didn't smoke that much in the first place but you know every cigarette is too much. May I ask your reason to stop smoking? (if that's to personal i understand) And how are you doing at your attempt

b70d6c6a-11b2-4a2c-9206-8a34a2b4bad8.text: Hooray! Fuck the cigarettes! I'm on week 4 of my 14the attempt to quit. Even if you smoke one, keep trying and take it day by day!
